questions.stem: Number of isomeric compounds with molecular formula $$C_9H_{10}O$$ which (i) do not dissolve in NaOH (ii) do not dissolve in HCl. (iii) do not give orange precipitate with 2, 4 â€“ DNP (iv) on hydrogenation give identical compound with molecular formula $$C_9H_{12}O$$ is __________.
questions.explanation: As per the question, the best possible isomeric structure is Ph-CH=CH-O-CH3 (cis and trans). Thus, there are 2 isomers that satisfy the conditions.
questions.tip_formula: For isomeric compounds, consider geometric isomers and structural isomers that meet all conditions stated.

questions.stem: The density of 3 M solution of NaCl is 1.0 g ml$$^{-1}$$. Molality of the solution is __________ $$\times 10^{-2}$$ m. (Nearest integer).
questions.explanation: Using the formula $$m = \frac{1000 \times M}{1000 \times d - M \times M.W.\text{ of solute}}$$, where M is 3, $$d = 1.0 g ml^{-1}$$, and M.W. is the molar weight of NaCl (58.5 g/mol), the molality is calculated as 3.64.
questions.tip_formula: Molality, $$m = \frac{1000 \times M}{1000 \times d - M \times M.W.\text{ of solute}}$$, where M is molarity.

questions.stem: Electrons in a cathode ray tube have been emitted with a velocity of 1000 m/s. The number of following statements which is/are true about the emitted radiation is
questions.explanation: (A) True, the deBroglie wavelength of the electron $$\lambda = \frac{h}{mv} = 666.67\text{ nm}$$; (B) False, the character of electrons emitted is independent of the cathode material; (C) True, cathode rays start from cathode and move toward anode; (D) False, the nature is independent of the gas in the tube.
